 bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/4/01 7:13:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> Didja get your +3 INT earrings in Qeynos from the Cuburt quest?  or do the Band of Rodcet nife in Qeynos?  There's a TON of quests in Qeynos for low levels.  Even if they're for other classes, you can sell the loot at the end, and even at lvl 10 they gave really good XP to me. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 29th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinnjatorix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/5/01 11:54:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> Done cuburt until i was bored of him <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Haven't done the band of rodcet nife though, maybe i will try<br>that one, shure would like to get my staff of wheel but i need to grow up first <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p>/Regards Berth (Sinnjatorix lvl 11 human wizard followér of solusek ro on luclin)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/8/01 9:23:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> Yeah, there's also a taxation quest for money and XP in qeynos, a few quests from the pally guild in SQ (bone chips in a box, and batwings I think) taht give good money when you sell the items back to merchants, and the plauge rat in the upper level of the merchant's house in NQ...  if you want quests, you just left the city for them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>At 11, i'd suggest working on Xp for a while - you're the perfect level to start joining dervish cutthroat groups in WC and NRo...  and when you get 3 derv rings, go to SRo, in the northwest corner, there's a single orc named &quot;Orillious&quot; or something close to that... he takes 3 rings at a time for XP and random loot (rusty to fine steel weapons, some rawhide armor).  If you kill any willowisps, hold onto the lightstones and glowing lightstones.  Keep one GLS for a light source, but take the rest to Oasis gypsy camp, or NK gypsy camp.  give them to Synthan (that's for sure her name) in Oasis one at a time, and you'll get a &quot;concordance of research&quot; (container) for GLSes, and books for lightstones.  Sell them back to her for as much money, or more, than you'd get for selling the same things to PCs, but you get XP for it too <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 29th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinnjatorix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/8/01 10:55:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> Done that rat in sneeds store, took forever to spawn and i got killed more then once <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  was level 2 at the time got a few copper in reward <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Been killing some wisps in EC and got a GLS, sold it to a merchant i admit <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  getting some nice xp for them, that concordance of research is that the one i will need for my research at lvl 16? research is fun when it works, but my main(necro) has failed his lvl 24 pet buff 3 times now, getting expensive to buy the words over and over, not to mention finding them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>/Regards Sinnjatorix <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/9/01 11:03:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> The concordance of research is ONLY for making practice runes.  If you give her a lightstone, she'll give you a book explaining how to make practice runes in the concordance, and then you take the practice runes in your lexicon to practice your research skill.  IF you decide to do this, start right away the 3rd level of practice runes - the first 2 don't help you get much of anywhere.  I put all my practice points into research, since the only other things not maxed are defense, offense, and piercing (I carry a weeping wand, 1hb). <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 30th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinnjatorix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/12/01 4:15:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> I have looked a little at the concordance quest, getting a GLS is not that hard, checked for my necro after fourth failure on that 24 pet buff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , some odd things needed to create the practice runes..<br><br> <p>/Regards Berth (Sinnjatorix lvl 12 human wizard <Ring of intrigue> luclin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/12/01 5:44:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> The practice runes do suck.  i started at the 3rd level practice runes, before I had a ton of regular ones in the bank...<br><br>I'd port to NRo, buy up as much spiderling silk, rawhide armor, zombie sking, and FS Weapons as I could, then run to WFP to buy Onyx's from the caster's guild, then port to GFay to buy Wasp Wings - you can buy 'em from newbies for like 1pp / stack - they're cheap.  I'd try to buy a few stacks, cause they're easier to get than anything else.  It cost a LOT of cash, but it got me a long ways up the skill ladder <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 30th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinnjatorix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/13/01 7:34:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> Since my last post i have failed the buff for the fifth time,<br>good news is that my skill did go up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Maybe the practice runes can be of use, but since i can't port yet it will be costly, think there is only one guy high enough in my guild that can port me.<br><br> <p>/Regards Berth (Sinnjatorix lvl 12 human wizard Ring of intrigue luclin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/15/01 9:01:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> Bind yourself in EFP, buy a port to GFay, buy 3 stacks of wasp wings, and gate yourself back to EFP to pick up everything else in NRo and freeport.  Camping the collapsed druid ring in NRo (where the undead stuff spawns) will get you the weapons, zombie skin, and sometimes raw-hide armor, or you can buy it off of newbies and the merchants.  Then you only have to pay for ports very rarely. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   if you're on Saryrn, I'd pop you over to GFay once no charge even - I'm in Freeport area often enough. eheh. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 30th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinnjatorix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/16/01 5:16:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quests for lowbie wizards</span><hr size=1> Thanks for that port offer, to bad i am on luclin, still i don't mind using my feet, did the run from qeynos -&gt; freeport,and i have been running from freeport -&gt; EW, still will be nice when i can port myself around..<br><br> <p>/Regards Berth (Sinnjatorix lvl 12 human wizard Ring of intrigue luclin</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=385.topic"